roomDetails.1: Minimal techno music is a simple subgenre of techno music. It is characterized by an abstract aesthetic that exploits the use of repetition and simple development. The minimalist technique is believed to have been originally developed in the early 1990s by Detroit-based producers Robert Hood and Daniel Bell.
roomDetails.2: Such trends saw the demise of the soul-infused techno that typified the original Detroit sound. Robert Hood has noted that he and Daniel Bell both realized something was missing from techno in the post-rave era.
